  "prompt": "What causes an invalid pregnancy test?",
  "response": "Several factors can cause an invalid pregnancy test result:\n\n1. Expired test\n- Test has passed its expiration date\n- Chemical components have degraded\n\n2. Improper storage\n- Exposed to extreme temperatures\n- High humidity\n- Direct sunlight\n\n3. User error\n- Not following instructions precisely\n- Testing too early\n- Not using first morning urine\n- Not waiting correct amount of time to read results\n- Diluted urine sample\n\n4. Test defect\n- Manufacturing error\n- Damaged packaging\n- Faulty test strip\n\n5. Medical conditions\n- Recent pregnancy loss\n- Certain medications\n- Certain medical treatments\n- Hormone imbalances\n\n6. Timing\n- Testing before missed period\n- Testing too soon after conception\n- Not waiting long enough after missed period\n\n7. Chemical interference\n- Some medications\n- Certain medical conditions\n- Protein or blood in urine\n\nIf you get an invalid result, it's recommended to:\n- Use a new test\n- Follow instructions carefully\n- Test again in a few days\n- Consult healthcare professional if uncertain",
